==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Liverpool]] and [[puddle]], as a pun on the "pool" of Liverpool.

===Adjective===
'''Liverpudlian''' (''no [[comparative]] or [[superlative]]'')

# Of or relating to [[Liverpool]] in the [[United Kingdom]].

====Synonyms====
*[[Scouse]] {{colloquial}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A native or resident of [[Liverpool]] in the [[United Kingdom]].

====Synonyms====
*[[Scouser]] {{colloquial}}

